<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="148" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[794,1399,1193,1665]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,907,1193,1217]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Comment</emphasis>
: The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[1215,1398,1193,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[1215,1398,1193,1217]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Drusilla brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a unique female from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1215,1317,1225,1249]" name="Thailand" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Thailand" name="Krung Thep Mahanakhon" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Bangkok</collectingRegion>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="PACE, R." box="[861,992,1257,1281]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" pagination="481 - 491" refId="ref58148" refString="PACE, R. 1986 b: Aleocharinae dell'Asia sudorientale raccolte dal Dr. Osella (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 11 [1984]: 481 - 491." type="journal article" year="1986">PACE 1986b</bibRefCitation>
) and that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[1135,1259,1257,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thainiger">
<emphasis box="[1135,1259,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Z. thainiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a unique female from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1045,1289,1313]" name="Thailand" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, Doi Mae Salong” (
<bibRefCitation author="PACE, R." box="[1255,1388,1289,1313]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" pagination="319 - 360" refId="ref59001" refString="PACE, R. 2012 b: New data, new species, and two new genera of Aleocharinae from the Oriental Region (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - Vernate 31: 319 - 360." type="journal article" year="2012">PACE 2012b</bibRefCitation>
). Judging from the labels attached to the 
<typeStatus box="[1268,1363,1321,1345]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Pace" authorityName=", Pace" authorityYear="1986" box="[794,977,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[794,915,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">D. brignolii</emphasis>
, Pace
</taxonomicName>
originally planned to name the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[794,891,1385,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osellai">
<emphasis box="[794,891,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">D. osellai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but later changed his mind. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pace" authorityYear="1986" box="[1214,1398,1385,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[1214,1398,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Drusilla brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was moved to 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu" authorityName="SenSU" box="[960,1090,1418,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1019,1418,1441]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Zyras</emphasis>
sensu
</taxonomicName>
strictu, primarily based on the illustration of the spermatheca, by 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[1221,1395,1449,1473]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" pagination="87 - 175" refId="ref57174" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 a: A revision of Zyras STEPHENS sensu strictu of China, Taiwan, and Hong Kong, with records and (re-) descriptions of some species from other regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 9: 87 - 175." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING (2016a)</bibRefCitation>
. A comparison of the 
<typeStatus box="[1030,1136,1481,1505]" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">holotypes</typeStatus>
revealed no differences whatsoever suggesting that they should belong to different species, so that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[1015,1139,1545,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thainiger">
<emphasis box="[1015,1139,1545,1569]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="148">Z. thainiger</emphasis>
